The user wants a TypeScript program for Node.js that solves the minimum cost path problem on a rectangular grid.

Input format:
- First line: H W (height and width)
- Next H lines: grid characters

Grid characters:
- 'S' = start
- 'T' = target
- '#' = wall
- '0'-'9' = passable cells with cost equal to the digit

Movement: up/down/left/right
Cost: sum of costs of entered digit cells. Entering 'S' or 'T' costs 0. The start cell itself contributes 0.
Output: Minimum cost from S to T, or -1 if unreachable.

Algorithm: Dijkstra's algorithm
- Priority queue to process cells in order of minimum cost
- Distance array initialized to infinity
- Start at 'S' with distance 0

Let's implement this in TypeScript.

```typescript
import { PriorityQueue } from 'priority-queue';
```
Wait, standard Node.js doesn't have a built-in priority queue in the standard library without external packages. I should implement a simple binary heap priority queue myself.

Let's write a simple min-heap priority queue in TypeScript.

```typescript
class PriorityQueue<T> {
    private heap: T[];
    private compare: (a: T, b: T) => number;

    constructor(compare: (a: T, b: T) => number) {
        this.heap = [];
        this.compare = compare;
    }

    push(item: T): void {
        this.heap.push(item);
        this.siftUp(this.heap.length - 1);
    }

    pop(): T | undefined {
        if (this.heap.length === 0) return undefined;
        const top = this.heap[0];
        const last = this.heap.pop()!;
        if (this.heap.length > 0) {
            this.heap[0] = last;
            this.siftDown(0);
        }
        return top;
    }

    private siftUp(index: number): void {
        const item = this.heap[index];
        while (index > 0) {
            const parentIndex = (index - 1) >> 1;
            const parent = this.heap[parentIndex];
            if (this.compare(item, parent) <= 0) {
                this.heap[index] = parent;
                index = parentIndex;
            } else {
                break;
            }
        }
        this.heap[index] = item;
    }

    private siftDown(index: number): void {
        const halfLength = this.heap.length >> 1;
        const item = this.heap[index];
        while (index < halfLength) {
            let leftChild = (index << 1) + 1;
            let rightChild = leftChild + 1;
            let smallest = leftChild;
            if (rightChild < this.heap.length && this.compare(this.heap[rightChild], this.heap[leftChild]) < 0) {
                smallest = rightChild;
            }
            if (this.compare(this.heap[smallest], item) < 0) {
                this.heap[index] = this.heap[smallest];
                index = smallest;
            } else {
                break;
            }
        }
        this.heap[index] = item;
    }

    isEmpty(): boolean {
        return this.heap.length === 0;
    }
}
```

